What is the equation of the following graph in terms of the tangent function?

\(y=\)[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]

generalfeedback.text: Notice that the graph follows the form of a tangent function. The first thing we can see is that it has period \(180^\circ\). Next notice that it has vertical asymptotes at \(120^\circ+180k^\circ\) for \(k \in \mathbb{Z}\) whereas the graph of \(\tan x\) has vertical asymptotes \(90^\circ+180k^\circ\), therefore this graph has been translated to the right by \(30^\circ\). Hence the equation of the graph is \[ y={@ta1@} \]
